AGI - Some people were injured on the market square in Mannheim, writes the Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung on its website. In the late morning there was an attack on several people on the market square in Mannheim where an anti-Islamic event had been held. It is not yet possible to provide information on the extent and severity of wounds. "The attacker then used a firearm. The attacker was also injured," the police reported.
&nbsp;
Mannheimer Morgen reported, citing a police spokesman on the spot, that the police officer was seriously injured. According to the police, there is no danger to the population. At the time of the crime the citizen movement Pax Europa was present with an information stand on the market square of Mannheim. On the Internet, video shows that the attacker has targeted the managers of the information stand. &nbsp;
&nbsp;
"My thoughts are with the victims," wrote Chancellor Olaf Scholz on X about the "terrible" that happened. "Violence is absolutely unacceptable in our democracy. The culprit must be severely punished."&nbsp;

