AGI - Berlin says yes to the use of German weapons to target Moscow on Russian territory. For the first time in an explicit manner, Germany directly authorizes Kiev to use weapons to stop the advance of Moscow forces. Italy confirms its 'no' and foreign minister, Antonio Tajani>, reaffirms the line of government: "We will continue to support Ukraine but we will not authorize the use of weapons to strike the Russian territory - says the vice-premier - the Constitution in Article 11 prohibits it. We are at the side of Kiev, but we are not at war with Moscow."
&nbsp;
On the other hand, the German position announced today: "Ukraine has the right, guaranteed by international law, to defend itself against Russian attacks and can also use the weapons provided for this purpose, including those we have delivered to it," said Chancellor Olaf Scholz>, Steffen Hebestreit, in a press release. "In recent weeks, Russia has prepared, coordinated and executed attacks, especially in the Kharkiv region, from positions in the Russian border area immediately adjacent," reads in the note. "Together we are convinced that Ukraine has the right, guaranteed by international law, to defend itself against these attacks," he added.
<h2 The turn of Biden marking a precedent
Germany, like other allied countries, had so far excluded the use of the weapons supplied in Kiev on the Russian territory, for fear of an escalation>, with the underlying threat of the <a href="https://www.agi.it/estero/news/2024-05-30/putin-russia-ucraine-bomba-atomic-explosion-demonstrative-26586858/"> use of the nuclear weapon But several countries have now changed their position from France, but also the United States. The opening of Berlin in fact arrives after the substantial freeway of the White House > reported by the main US media: According to the Washington Post and the New York Times, American President Joe Biden>, in an important change urged by his advisers and major allies, authorized Ukraine to conduct limited attacks within the Russian territory with American manufacturing weapons, opening up to what could be a new chapter of the war.
&nbsp;
The <a href="https://www.agi.it/estero/news/2024-05-30/ucraina-biden-autorizza-uso-armi-colpire-russia-26588420/"> Biden's decision, if confirmed, would mark an absolute precedent >: for the first time an American president would allow limited military responses within the borders of an opponent with nuclear weapons. White House officials, however, insisted that the authorization extends only to those that are defined acts of self-defense, in particular to allow Kiev troops to defend Kharkiv and surrounding areas from missiles, planant bombs and artillery bullets launched from across the border.
&nbsp;
Ukrainian forces are already using US weapons to attack Russia, is the Kremlin response. "We know that, in general, American manufacturing weapons are already used to attempt attacks on Russian territory. And this is a fairly eloquent proof of the extent of US involvement in this conflict," said the press spokesman of the Kremlin, Dmitry Peskov>. And the Vice-President of the Russian Security Council, Dmitry Medvedev>, threatens: "NATO is now part of the conflict, the use of tactical nuclear weapons by Moscow is not a bluff."

